QUICK REFERENCE HANDBOOK - QRH
Preface
Purpose
A Quick Reference Handbook (QRH) is a handbook containing extracts
from the Flight Crew Operating Manual which may need to be referred
to quickly and/or frequently, usually including Emergency, Abnormal,
and Normal procedures.
Inflight Performance, Operational Data, and
Supplementary Data is also included.
Intended User
The intended user for the Quick Reference Handbook (QRH) are Virgin
America Pilots and Flight Operations teammates.
Expectations
Policies and procedures contained within the Quick Reference
Handbook (QRH), which is part of the Virgin America Manual System,
are expected to be used by Virgin America teammates, and business
partners.
Security Settings
This publication has been locked down for security purposes, in a read
only format, using password protection. Printing is allowed. Copying of
text, images, and other content is not allowed. Repurposing of content
is limited as noted in GM 02.
